{
  "name": "emotional_state",
  "description": "Persistent emotional/arousal state using bistable CH ring. Implements 'I AM scared' (not 'I see danger'). The bistable ring (a=0, c=-65, d=0) sustains for hundreds of ticks after a brief trigger, providing sustained modulatory bias to the brain. Can represent fear, hunger, curiosity, etc. Multiple emotional_state instances can compete via mutual inhibition (use state_machine_3 pattern). Use case: sustained arousal after threat, persistent food-seeking drive, curiosity bias. The output modulates other components via diffuse weak connections, lowering thresholds globally (scared = jump at shadows) or biasing specific pathways.",
